``   as heavily. Psiblast = 2 rounds lag.
3) T-port will not work if you're cursed.
4) Derandomized slayers spells damage.
5) Esper spell mod is now 120%. Booyaka!
6) Trip and footsweep can be used while flying, again. Footsweep lag altered.

Takes effect on reboot.
~
Sender  Kevin~
Date    Wed Jun  5 18:34:24 2002~
Stamp   1023320064
To      all~
Subject Gains.~
Text
Lately, a lot of people have shown displeasure for the current gains.
Mana and movement were based on stats, and further modified by class.

First of all, a more or less obvious change.
Amulet of the Ancients now adds 30 hp/mana/movement.

I have centralized HP/Mana/Movement gains to be based on class, and then modified by Con/Wis/Dex.
Demons now get double HP at level-up, like it says in the helpfile.
The existing HP ranges have been adjusted upwards, some classes getting a larger boost than others.

"What does it all mean, uncle Kevin?"
It means you will see greater mana gains, ESPECIALLY in clerics and mages.
It means you will see greater move gains, ESPECIALLY in ninjas and monks.
It means you will see greater HP gains, ESPECIALLY in demons.

The actual modifiers I used for mana and movement are close to what I had planned for the new stats system.

- `&K`7evin, who keeps an eye on those who remake.
P.S. Those of you who helped test the gains, I commented out the extra code from score.
~
