Date    Fri Aug  2 21:09:36 2002~
Stamp   1028340576
To      all~
Subject An update of yesterday's change~
Text
Olds:
Demons and espers are back to the way they were.
Demon HP gains are different. 1.3x for thieves/ninjas, 1.6x for warriors.

News:
Res/vuln plays a less important role in saving throws.
The 'diminishing returns' on saves has been changed as well.
Res/vuln damage mods in spells have been lowered to those of physical
attacks: 80/120 percent, respectively.
High Elves get a 10% damage bonus with their spells.
Ra-tilt alternates between HOLY and LIGHT damage, with equal chances of either type being used per hit.

These changes were tested on 9010 with Fatetaf and 6-7 players, who gave me the go-ahead.
~
Sender  Kevin~
Date    Mon Aug 19 22:46:36 2002~
Stamp   1029815196
To      all~
Subject Stuff as of 8/19/02~
Text
Gun magazines have been removed from the code.
A new gun caliber has been added: 12 gauge, in buckshot/slug flavors.
Anyone with a DEAD flag will lose it when completing an autoquest.
Demi/gravija have returned to their old damage calls, and can be scribed no more than once on a scroll.
Black hole damage has been lowered, and will now hit 3 times at 90.
Changed how OLC writes an object's condition value to area files.
Changed how the mud reads an object's condition value into memory.
Added an NPC check to Tport. They can't use it anymore.
Toyed with RoT/Demonfire's damage a bit, more changes pending.
Fixed an issue with unload.
Esper clerics and mages get the 120% spell bonus, monks only get 110%.

I'm tired, so I'm going to sleep soon.
~
